  ],
  "literals": {
    "row_status": "Active"
  },
  "notes": "Source table neuract__FM_TABLE stores six flow meter channels in wide format (FM_101..FM_106 for readings, FM_101_TOTALIZER..FM_106_TOTALIZER for cumulative values). A single MELT rule unpivots all twelve value columns into 6 long rows per timestamp, producing row_meter_id (the column name string label), row_reading (m3/h value), and row_totalizer (m3 cumulative value). row_status has no catalog source and is injected as the static constant 'Active' via literals. total_flow is computed as SUM(row_totalizer) across all six melted rows via totals_math — it has no direct single-column mapping."
